Aaron Hernandez was found guilty Wednesday of first-degree murder in the 2013 shooting death of semi-professional football player Odin Lloyd . 
  The 25-year-old is accused of killing Daniel Abreu and Safirdo Furtado in a 2012 drive-by shooting in South Boston . 
  Hernandez was sentenced to life in prison without the possibility of parole in the death of Lloyd . 
  He will face a second trial in Boston later this year in the killings of the two immigrants . 
  The two men were killed in July 2012 after a fight at a nightclub over a spilled drink . 
 